To implement the robot factory settings with the required constraints, we need to introduce a way to track used names globally and store the current name within each `Robot` instance. 

Since the `name()` method takes `&self` but must lazily generate a name on the first call, we must use interior mutability (via `std::sync::Mutex`) to store the name. To satisfy the return type `&str` while using a `Mutex`, we use a small `unsafe` block to extend the lifetime of the returned reference to match the lifetime of the `Robot` instance. This is safe because the Rust borrow checker prevents `reset_name(&mut self)` from being called while any reference from `name(&self)` is still active.

For randomness without external crates, I have implemented a simple Linear Congruential Generator (LCG) seeded with the current system time.

Here are the changes:

lib.rs
```
use std::collections::HashSet;
use std::sync::{Mutex, OnceLock};
use std::time::SystemTime;

struct SimpleRng {
    state: u64,
}

impl SimpleRng {
    fn new() -> Self {
        let seed = SystemTime::now()
            .duration_since(SystemTime::UNIX_EPOCH)
            .unwrap()
            .as_nanos() as u64;
        Self { state: seed }
    }

    fn next_u32(&mut self) -> u32 {
        self.state = self.state.wrapping_mul(6364136223846793005).wrapping_add(1);
        (self.state >> 32) as u32
    }
}

static USED_NAMES: OnceLock<Mutex<HashSet<String>>> = OnceLock::new();
static RNG: OnceLock<Mutex<SimpleRng>> = OnceLock::new();

fn get_used_names() -> &'static Mutex<HashSet<String>> {
    USED_NAMES.get_or_init(|| Mutex::new(HashSet::new()))
}

fn get_rng() -> &'static Mutex<SimpleRng> {
    RNG.get_or_init(|| Mutex::new(SimpleRng::new()))
}

pub struct Robot {
    name: Mutex<Option<String>>,
}

impl Robot {
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        Robot {
            name: Mutex::new(None),
        }
    }

    pub fn name(&self) -> &str {
        let mut guard = self.name.lock().unwrap();
        
        if guard.is_none() {
            loop {
                let mut candidate = String::with_capacity(5);
                {
                    let mut rng = get_rng().lock().unwrap();
                    for _ in 0..2 {
                        candidate.push((rng.next_u32() as u8 % 26 + b'A') as char);
                    }
                    for _ in 0..3 {
                        candidate.push((rng.next_u32() as u8 % 10 + b'0') as char);
                    }
                }

                let mut used = get_used_names().lock().unwrap();
                if !used.contains(&candidate) {
                    used.insert(candidate.clone());
                    *guard = Some(candidate);
                    break;
                }
            }
        }

        let s = guard.as_ref().unwrap();
        // Safety: The borrow checker ensures that reset_name(&mut self) cannot be called
        // while this reference is held, as it requires an exclusive borrow.
        unsafe { std::mem::transmute::<&str, &str>(s) }
    }

    pub fn reset_name(&mut self) {
        *self.name.lock().unwrap() = None;
    }
}
