I will update `PhoneNumber.java` to include validation logic that adheres to the North American Numbering Plan (NANP) rules and satisfies the failing tests.

Specifically, I will:
1.  Validate that the input string only contains allowed characters (digits, spaces, hyphens, dots, parentheses, and the plus sign). Any other characters (like letters or special symbols) will trigger an `IllegalArgumentException`.
2.  Extract all digits from the input.
3.  Handle the country code: if the digit sequence is 11 digits long, it must start with '1'. If it does, the '1' is removed. If it doesn't, an `IllegalArgumentException` is thrown.
4.  Ensure the resulting digit sequence is exactly 10 digits long.
5.  Validate the Area Code: the first digit (index 0) must be between 2 and 9.
6.  Validate the Exchange Code: the first digit of the exchange code (index 3) must be between 2 and 9.

PhoneNumber.java
```
class PhoneNumber {
    private final String number;

    PhoneNumber(String numberString) {
        // Validate that the input contains only allowed characters
        // Allowed: digits, whitespace, hyphens, dots, parentheses, and plus sign
        if (!numberString.matches("[0-9\\s\\-\\.\\(\\)\\+]*")) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Phone number contains invalid characters");
        }

        // Extract only the digits
        String digits = numberString.replaceAll("[^0-9]", "");

        // Handle country code: if 11 digits, it must start with '1'
        if (digits.length() == 11) {
            if (!digits.startsWith("1")) {
                throw new IllegalArgumentException("11-digit numbers must start with country code 1");
            }
            digits = digits.substring(1);
        }

        // The resulting number must be exactly 10 digits
        if (digits.length() != 10) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Phone number must be 10 digits long (excluding country code)");
        }

        // Validate Area Code (NXX): N must be 2-9
        char areaCodeFirstDigit = digits.charAt(0);
        if (areaCodeFirstDigit < '2' || areaCodeFirstDigit > '9') {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Area code must start with a digit between 2 and 9");
        }

        // Validate Exchange Code (NXX): N must be 2-9
        char exchangeCodeFirstDigit = digits.charAt(3);
        if (exchangeCodeFirstDigit < '2' || exchangeCodeFirstDigit > '9') {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Exchange code must start with a digit between 2 and 9");
        }

        this.number = digits;
    }

    String getNumber() {
        return this.number;
    }

}
```
